             South Korea, Asiaâ€™s third-biggest
buyer of base metals, issued a tender to buy 6,000 metric tons
of high-grade primary aluminum, according to notices on the
website of a state agency.  
 The Public Procurement Service, which stockpiles strategic
commodities, is seeking offers from suppliers by June 24, the
agency said. Shipment is due in July and August, it said.  
